Forwarded from: Do SOMETHING to liberate Belarus!
I congratulate the Kalinowski regiment on its two-year anniversary!

I myself am no longer in the regiment, but the path I traveled in the "Volat" battalion of the Kalinovsky regiment will remain with me forever.

This path is one of the intangible values of my life. It is valuable because during it I:

- WAS TOGETHER with the guys who took up arms to stop the Russian horde today in Ukraine, tomorrow in Belarus;
- MET personally with those who are no longer with us or are still in captivity (such as "Tick" and "Trombley";
- GAINED military experience that I can use for the benefit of Belarus;
- I UNDERSTOOD how my body feels in battle;
- REVIEWED his values through difficult trials.

I wish the guys, both newcomers and those who have been through more than one battle, to complete all the tasks and at the same time save themselves (their lives, their physical and psychological health).

Belarus needs real Belarusians, who not only bring the defeat of Russia as an empire with words, but also sacrifice their personal well-being, risking their health and life on this path.

I congratulate all Kolino residents on the day of formation of the regiment!
